fix: VIX threshold overhaul, 26 bug fixes from deep code review

VIX gating:
- Split extreme bucket into extreme (30-35, SHORT-only) and panic (35+, hard stop)
- Add VIX_BEARISH_CONFIRMATION_THRESHOLD for high-confidence SHORT direction
- Add FVG-edge SL fallback for displacement moves when swing SL fails RR

Critical and High bug fixes:
- Same-bar SL+TP outcome uses distance-based resolution instead of always LOSS
- Silent except pass on displacement validation now rejects FVG on failure
- DB failure no longer suppresses trade alerts
- Calendar fetch failure warns via Telegram when news filter is inactive
- Dedup race condition fixed with shared lock between is_duplicate and log_signal
- Orderflow divergence no longer inflates L4 score when delta contradicts
- Failed system alerts no longer deduped so they retry on next cycle
- _run_async returns success bool for accurate send logging
- Weekly retrain split into 3 isolated try blocks
- Symbol lookup uses exact match instead of substring
- Calendar date matching uses startswith instead of substring

Medium fixes:
- HARD_STOP latch log message corrected
- get_sl_time silent except now logs errors
- macro_checker fallback blocks trading consistently
- Stale macro cache no longer resets TTL
- Outcome tracker warns when timestamp column missing
- Wyckoff guards against NaN and zero volume
- PDH PDL fetch increased to 72 H1 bars
- SL validated on correct side of price
- DST warning logged at startup
- send_system_alert wrapped in nested try in main loop

641 tests passing, 0 regressions.
